The paper discusses the design and implementation of a mixed-signal neuron for neuromorphic computing, which falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the trade-offs between digital and analog/mixed-signal neurons, which relates to the field of electronic devices and circuits (cs.ET). Additionally, the paper discusses the noise and variability in the proposed neuron, which relates to the field of computer architecture (cs.AR) and circuit design (cs.CE). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed neuron on a classification task, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
